e0bf3a68-3f74-5367-8249-eee0e68c4384.description: This is the first numeric keypad in the Jacdac system, featuring an OLED screen, a rotary encoder, RGB LED lighting, and one Jacdac interface. It is powered by the RP2040 microcontroller.

The Air Quality Index is a measure of how clean or polluted air is. From min, good quality, to high, low quality.
The range of AQI may vary between countries (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_quality_index).

d1f0c076-5adf-507c-8ec2-88eeffdefd30.title: AW Agent
d1f0c076-5adf-507c-8ec2-88eeffdefd30.description: AW Agent, short for AgileWhisker Agent, is a small software for PC computers that is designed to be used in conjunction with AgileWhisker Keyboard Elite60 and other keyboards. It is an open-source software. It functions as a virtual hardware within the jacdac ecosystem. It incorporates MQTT services to retrieve hardware information from the computer and trigger computer events, among other functionalities.

890d98df-94f4-5fae-b685-1f0d967ad68e.description:

A gamepad with direction and action buttons for one player.
If a device has multiple controllers, it should have multiple gamepad services, using consecutive service identifiers.

bd0d6d4b-5c68-5418-ae50-e3bfcb8da45e.title: DuckyBot Kit
bd0d6d4b-5c68-5418-ae50-e3bfcb8da45e.description: Dive into the enchanting world of robotics with DuckyBot, a delightful cardboard robot shaped like a cheerful yellow duck. Engineered around the groundbreaking Jacdac Elite Module Suite, DuckyBot offers young learners a quirky and entertaining gateway into the vast realm of electronics and robotics, integrating seamlessly with Microbit and Makecode platforms.

cfebbd03-1813-585e-bd57-759598c60da0.title: Arcade Sound
cfebbd03-1813-585e-bd57-759598c60da0.description:
A sound playing device.

10315447-25ed-5cfe-aca2-b40ccbdceadc.title: Env Sensor
10315447-25ed-5cfe-aca2-b40ccbdceadc.description: Env Sensor is a device used to measure both the temperature and humidity of the surrounding environment.

74b798e9-536f-5abe-8516-68715e49070a.title: Barcode reader
74b798e9-536f-5abe-8516-68715e49070a.description: A device that reads various barcodes, like QR codes. For the web, see [BarcodeDetector](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/BarcodeDetector).

Its core is the ESP32, which has the characteristics of high performance, wireless communication, and graphical programming.

e552eb3a-f9de-5aab-aa85-cfaac385bd91.title: bit:radio
e552eb3a-f9de-5aab-aa85-cfaac385bd91.description: Support for sending and receiving packets using the [Bit Radio protocol](https://github.com/microsoft/pxt-common-packages/blob/master/libs/radio/docs/reference/radio.md), typically used between micro:bit devices.

3a4d3b11-84e6-58ed-a4ab-7facf53bce05.title: Haptic Output
3a4d3b11-84e6-58ed-a4ab-7facf53bce05.description: The Haptic Output module is essentially a vibration motor that can be used to provide haptic feedback in electronic devices.

2221233e-7fdf-54c5-890b-b36b9fb74889.title: Bootloader
2221233e-7fdf-54c5-890b-b36b9fb74889.description:
Allows flashing (reprogramming) devices over Jacdac.

This is typically implemented by having a separate _bootloader_ mode, as opposed to _application_ mode
on the module to be flashed.
The bootloader mode is entered on every device reset, for about 300ms.
The bootloader will generally not announce itself, until it gets some command.
Once it gets the command, it will stay in application mode.

Typically, you ask the module (in application mode) to reset, while sending broadcast
`info` commands to all bootloaders every 100ms or so.
Alternatively, you ask the the user to disconnect and re-connect the module, while
broadcasting `info` commands.
The second method works even if the application is damaged (eg., due to an aborted flash).

When device is in bootloader mode, the device ID may change compared to application mode,
by flipping the first bit in the first byte of the device identifier.

d8e739f8-12f8-512f-8dc4-b1a0fe46beeb.title: Braille display
d8e739f8-12f8-512f-8dc4-b1a0fe46beeb.description: A Braille pattern display module. This module display [unicode braille patterns](https://www.unicode.org/charts/PDF/U2800.pdf), country specific encoding have to be implemented by the clients.

824e301a-f290-5126-96fe-41d68e833da1.description: Indicates that the device acts as a bridge to the Jacdac bus.

9641d3e8-1617-5ad8-9557-d2b623e96d23.description: A configuration service for a capacitive push-button.

Supports cloud connections to upload and download data.
Note that `f64` values following a label are not necessarily aligned.

18473d86-291a-552e-97fe-cf6eed3a1c18.title: NanoScript 2040
18473d86-291a-552e-97fe-cf6eed3a1c18.description: Elevate your embedded projects with our cutting-edge development board, powered by Raspberry Pi's RP2040 and tailored for DeviceScript. Experience the unmatched synergy of TypeScript in the realm of microcontroller programming, where precision, efficiency, and modern development practices converge.

c328eb88-084e-56b4-91f9-ec485493ce92.title: Cloud Configuration
c328eb88-084e-56b4-91f9-ec485493ce92.description: Connection and diagnostics information about the cloud connection.

4e6f8245-5a02-5607-aad4-73fe4bef15eb.description: KittenBot Newbit Arcade Shield is an expansion board developed exclusively for Micro:bit V2. Equipped with the Newbit Arcade Shield, you can use Micro:bit to design games online in MakeCodeArcade, or play games offline, which will broaden your experience of programming with Micro:bit V2.

ec567281-6f7f-5cc5-be3a-96742cd2c1e7.title: CODAL Message Bus
ec567281-6f7f-5cc5-be3a-96742cd2c1e7.description:
A service that uses the [CODAL message bus](https://lancaster-university.github.io/microbit-docs/ubit/messageBus/) to send and receive small messages.

You can find known values for `source` in [CODAL repository](https://github.com/lancaster-university/codal-core/blob/master/inc/core/CodalComponent.h)
In MakeCode, you can listen for custom `source`, `value` values using [control.onEvent](https://makecode.microbit.org/reference/control/on-event].

633f1586-3dca-58af-8d47-dbd063a88cd4.title: Power
633f1586-3dca-58af-8d47-dbd063a88cd4.description: Power module is used to supply high-current JACDAC modules such as servo modules.It can also be used to supply power to the entire JACDAC electronic system.It has overcurrent protection and a maximum output current of 1A.

4742d854-b049-5b1b-a194-c70044bafe8b.title: Relay
4742d854-b049-5b1b-a194-c70044bafe8b.description:
This relay module is designed for low voltage and low current applications. It's recommended to use a voltage of 5V and a current no greater than 1A.
When using a relay module, it's important to be aware of electrical safety. It's recommended that you use the relay module under adult supervision, especially if you are not familiar with electrical circuits and how to use them safely.

361ada25-14a0-59ef-b885-fe2396784a82.title: Compass
361ada25-14a0-59ef-b885-fe2396784a82.description: A sensor that measures the heading.

0f8e9a5b-50d9-51b6-8eba-ab5e6bb8b1a0.title: RGB Ring
0f8e9a5b-50d9-51b6-8eba-ab5e6bb8b1a0.description: A ring of 8 colored programmable LEDs.

090622d0-4d77-5edc-b2be-0e057b6c07ab.description:

It handles actions common to all services on a device.

Note: some of the optional features (including `flood_ping`, `mcu_temperature`, and all string registers)
are not implemented in `8bit` version.

d7662512-37ec-552d-93a8-b18854dbfb56.description: RGB Strip module is used to drive WS2812 LED strips. If you're driving a large number of LEDs, such as more than 10, it's recommended to provide additional power to the LED strip to ensure stable and reliable operation.

3641df1d-dcb2-547d-a7a0-dae6cd2dcf70.title: Cursor Character Screen
3641df1d-dcb2-547d-a7a0-dae6cd2dcf70.description: An addressable LCD screen, with cursor position.

14aeee58-94f1-55fb-9c77-63946b2a7dd3.description: Servo module is used to drive standard 3-wire analog servos. It has two output channels and can operate in two different current output modes: 500mA and 1A.

ca9ead97-f721-5951-84d9-941ab79402a9.description:
Conditions are synthetic services used to synchronize threads of executions of a DeviceScript VM.
**This is no longer used**.

e5b90be3-4c83-5a34-af9c-1839b7b02ad1.description: Allows for inspecting and affecting the state of a running DeviceScript program.

b8ca0987-292c-5fc5-97b8-f279ec7ddbe9.title: DeviceScript Manager
b8ca0987-292c-5fc5-97b8-f279ec7ddbe9.description:
Allows for deployment and control over DeviceScript virtual machine.

Programs start automatically after device restart or uploading of new program.
You can stop programs until next reset by setting the `running` and `autostart` registers to `false`.

0f3fa189-fdf4-5f23-8a19-98ec21c828f6.description: This Forward Education Jacdac sensor monitors when water reaches a specific level. It uses a simple internal float that activates a signal at a set water height. Your project reads this signal through the Jacdac connection to know the level status.

1391b5fa-b6c4-5fca-975e-aaabb72a2240.description: A two axis directional gamepad with optional buttons.

44b69d32-4432-5404-8e4f-b7639334d3a8.title: Learn to Solder Kit
44b69d32-4432-5404-8e4f-b7639334d3a8.description: Learn to solder by assembling this module's through-hole components yourself. 524302e1-9102-5512-9831-551a29ff60ab.title: GPIO
524302e1-9102-5512-9831-551a29ff60ab.description:

The pins are indexed `0 ... num_pins-1`.
The indexing does not correspond to hardware pin names, nor labels on the board (see `get_pin_info` command for that),
and should **not** be exposed to the user.

bf30a36f-95a3-52a2-960c-97ecdb7632d6.title: LED Lights
bf30a36f-95a3-52a2-960c-97ecdb7632d6.description: LED Lights is a ws2812 LED ring compatible with the Jacdac framework and part of the Climate Action Kit by Forward Education

b9c444aa-c3ef-597f-b3e8-39f41b1f2ab2.title: Lights
b9c444aa-c3ef-597f-b3e8-39f41b1f2ab2.description: Control dimmable LED light strips with the Forward Education Jacdac "Lights" module.  It uses an external 5V or 12V power supply to safely power and manage brightness levels for your LEDs.  Integrate and command your lighting easily through the standard Jacdac connection.

1b8401a5-2f55-5ea1-9734-979d53d88d5c.title: Heart Rate
1b8401a5-2f55-5ea1-9734-979d53d88d5c.description:
A sensor approximating the heart rate. 


**Jacdac is NOT suitable for medical devices and should NOT be used in any kind of device to diagnose or treat any medical conditions.**

95f7684b-a7f0-523e-8d67-0c0650d93828.title: Line Sensor
95f7684b-a7f0-523e-8d67-0c0650d93828.description: Line Sensor is a multi-reflected light sensor compatible with the Jacdac framework and part of the Climate Action Kit by Forward Education

2002a5a4-7a72-5fd5-8638-3046f8e10ac2.title: HID Keyboard
2002a5a4-7a72-5fd5-8638-3046f8e10ac2.description:
Control a HID keyboard.

The codes for the key (selectors) is defined in the [HID Keyboard
specification](https://usb.org/sites/default/files/hut1_21.pdf), chapter 10 Keyboard/Keypad Page, page 81.
Modifiers are in page 87.

The device keeps tracks of the key state and is able to clear it all with the clear command.

a210348f-8278-5225-9d68-5472661fd283.title: Humidity
a210348f-8278-5225-9d68-5472661fd283.description: A sensor measuring humidity of outside environment.

595a7e1a-3346-5e8d-8ced-cb21a7357125.description: RPM Sensor is a sensor module compatible with the Jacdac framework and part of the module ecosystem by Forward Education

Inter-Integrated Circuit (I2C, I²C, IIC) serial communication bus lets you communicate with

86b1fc21-3d1a-5827-9aec-9f950905e2e8.description: Solar Sensor is a photoresistor sensor compatible with the Jacdac framework and part of the Climate Action Kit by Forward Education

Note that this is different from _luminance_, the amount of light that passes through, emits from, or reflects off an object.

5b8da8d6-0749-5be3-9ebc-398a05b9d52b.description: Touch Sensor is a capacitive touch sensor compatible with the Jacdac framework and part of the Climate Action Kit by Forward Education

48b7615e-cea3-5070-bf1f-fe8608858b62.title: LED
48b7615e-cea3-5070-bf1f-fe8608858b62.description:
A controller for displays of individually controlled RGB LEDs.

For 64 or less LEDs, the service should support the pack the pixels in the pixels register.
Beyond this size, the register should return an empty payload as the amount of data exceeds
the size of a packet. Typically services that use more than 64 LEDs
will run on the same MCU and will maintain the pixels buffer internally.

f11de3fc-37a0-5517-aecf-8a2b306f88a0.title: Jacdac:bit
f11de3fc-37a0-5517-aecf-8a2b306f88a0.description: Jacdac:bit is a micro:bit interface module for easy connection to Jacdac devices, ideal for learning and interactive projects.

977ff735-c482-5ae3-874f-4f370f4d85cb.title: LED Single
977ff735-c482-5ae3-874f-4f370f4d85cb.description: A controller for 1 or more monochrome or RGB LEDs connected in parallel.

b61f397a-0a9e-5dfc-845f-e2be118c718c.title: LED Strip
b61f397a-0a9e-5dfc-845f-e2be118c718c.description: A controller for strips of individually controlled RGB LEDs.

124d0a77-dae1-5036-aba5-cecf516f10a4.title: Light level
124d0a77-dae1-5036-aba5-cecf516f10a4.description: A sensor that measures luminosity level.

27db7885-d39c-5bdf-bb0c-4f419abfd74d.title: Logger
27db7885-d39c-5bdf-bb0c-4f419abfd74d.description: A service which can report messages to the bus.

82485e2a-194d-5fd0-8758-ac1385bb4555.title: Magnetic field level
82485e2a-194d-5fd0-8758-ac1385bb4555.description: A sensor that measures strength and polarity of magnetic field.

807784ff-eb53-50c5-80cf-6df9857d9a46.title: Matrix Keypad
807784ff-eb53-50c5-80cf-6df9857d9a46.description: A matrix of buttons connected as a keypad

84e45b56-da7d-5fd7-8a9c-087329f85e8e.title: Jacdac Power
84e45b56-da7d-5fd7-8a9c-087329f85e8e.description: The power module supplies high-current JACDAC devices like servos, powers the entire system, has overcurrent protection, and offers up to 1A output.

46000ad1-56c1-5317-88ce-dcf89bddef7e.title: Model Runner
46000ad1-56c1-5317-88ce-dcf89bddef7e.description:
Runs machine learning models.

Only models with a single input tensor and a single output tensor are supported at the moment.
Input is provided by Sensor Aggregator service on the same device.
Multiple instances of this service may be present, if more than one model format is supported by a device.

f4f4e80a-4e8b-53c5-940d-2530bfc2d3f9.title: Motion
f4f4e80a-4e8b-53c5-940d-2530bfc2d3f9.description: A sensor, typically PIR, that detects object motion within a certain range

d2019ee2-7599-5f95-8ef1-061752594bf2.title: Multitouch
d2019ee2-7599-5f95-8ef1-061752594bf2.description: A capacitive touch sensor with multiple inputs.

6719f663-fed6-50e2-843d-2e2aabd2fa25.title: micro:bit Retro Programming Arcade
6719f663-fed6-50e2-843d-2e2aabd2fa25.description: micro:bit Retro Arcade is a color screen joystick expansion board for micro:bit V2, it contains a TFT 160*128 color screen, 4 directional buttons, two A/B buttons and a reset button. micro:bit Retro Arcade can be used with micro:bit V2 to program games online and play offline on the Microsoft Arcade programming platform. It is a simple and fun way to help children write their own games and understand the mystery behind them. It also supports custom game characters, diverse scenarios and plot design using graphical programming software, making it easy for everyone to achieve fun electronic creations and unlimited game ideas. micro:bit Retro Arcade can also be used as a remote control handle in addition to a game programming learning machine.

4b4ea937-26e8-5f7e-bed7-7728c21f75a7.title: PC controller
4b4ea937-26e8-5f7e-bed7-7728c21f75a7.description: Send various events to PC, including opening a URL, start an app, sending text, etc.

56b0e079-5cb1-50eb-aaf0-a1e346c8f6f8.title: Smart Exploration Kit
56b0e079-5cb1-50eb-aaf0-a1e346c8f6f8.description: Help beginners get started quickly with the micro:bit and stimulate their interest in programming and electronic components

da73defc-7695-5135-91b8-a0bd20a5f220.title: Calliope mini V3
da73defc-7695-5135-91b8-a0bd20a5f220.description: Calliope mini is an easy-to-program microcontroller that has quite a few internal sensors and, in addition to a pin header and two Grove connectors it also features two JacDac connectors to connect sensors and actuators directly to the board.

865f260b-a281-5fe5-a024-8c0e20b4f5b2.title: Planar position
865f260b-a281-5fe5-a024-8c0e20b4f5b2.description:
A sensor that repors 2D position, typically an optical mouse tracking sensor.

The sensor starts at an arbitrary origin (0,0) and reports the distance from that origin.

The `streaming_interval` is respected when the position is changing. When the position is not changing, the streaming interval may be throttled to `500ms`.

703b1d96-3e04-5c43-9d1a-4a60d4c6e5e3.title: JM Base
703b1d96-3e04-5c43-9d1a-4a60d4c6e5e3.description: A breadboard like PCB to screw mount Jacdac modules.

db28ab64-caf1-57ad-ba29-7ab2e8d977ad.title: Power supply
db28ab64-caf1-57ad-ba29-7ab2e8d977ad.description: A power supply with a fixed or variable voltage range

ec9699b5-6dfb-5e60-a966-f63da306d253.title: Protocol Test
ec9699b5-6dfb-5e60-a966-f63da306d253.description:
This is test service to validate the protocol packet transmissions between the browser and a MCU.
Use this page if you are porting Jacdac to a new platform.

445a310d-9fc0-54db-adad-cb0ad5179dd7.title: Proxy
445a310d-9fc0-54db-adad-cb0ad5179dd7.description:
A service that tags a device as a packet proxy.
A device in proxy mode will proxy Jacdac packets and typically has its core logic halted.

2563cc74-ef7f-5082-8fc4-a98390267d13.title: Pulse Oximeter
2563cc74-ef7f-5082-8fc4-a98390267d13.description:
A sensor approximating the oxygen level.

**Jacdac is not suitable for medical devices and should NOT be used in any kind of device to diagnose or treat any medical conditions.**

cec72412-602e-584a-8387-a76038d2865d.title: Rain gauge
cec72412-602e-584a-8387-a76038d2865d.description: Measures the amount of liquid precipitation over an area in a predefined period of time.

7e8c4c23-ed39-5705-b7df-f8a049a41031.title: Real time clock
7e8c4c23-ed39-5705-b7df-f8a049a41031.description: Real time clock to support collecting data with precise time stamps.

dea2fbf7-ba30-50a2-8304-fc949c29788e.title: Reflected light
dea2fbf7-ba30-50a2-8304-fc949c29788e.description: A sensor that detects light and dark surfaces, commonly used for line following robots.

f7f5546d-311f-515e-b6d5-7932dcd99d5d.title: Relay
f7f5546d-311f-515e-b6d5-7932dcd99d5d.description:
A switching relay.

The contacts should be labelled `NO` (normally open), `COM` (common), and `NC` (normally closed).
When relay is energized it connects `NO` and `COM`.
When relay is not energized it connects `NC` and `COM`.
Some relays may be missing `NO` or `NC` contacts.
When relay module is not powered, or is in bootloader mode, it is not energized (connects `NC` and `COM`).

54c71d1f-902c-511e-9a91-eed991c1dc26.title: Random Number Generator
54c71d1f-902c-511e-9a91-eed991c1dc26.description:
Generates random numbers using entropy sourced from physical processes.

This typically uses a cryptographical pseudo-random number generator (for example [Fortuna](<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fortuna_(PRNG)>)),
which is periodically re-seeded with entropy coming from some hardware source.

3e53f938-914d-539e-b9d2-9bd400a0918c.title: Role Manager
3e53f938-914d-539e-b9d2-9bd400a0918c.description: Assign roles to services on the Jacdac bus.

9ca8c87d-37b4-52fa-9ad1-39a097213c1e.title: ROS
9ca8c87d-37b4-52fa-9ad1-39a097213c1e.description: A ROS (Robot Operating System https://www.ros.org/) controller that can act as a broker for messages.

fd8da769-11e1-589c-8808-6e0a4f898741.title: Rotary encoder
fd8da769-11e1-589c-8808-6e0a4f898741.description: An incremental rotary encoder - converts angular motion of a shaft to digital signal.

6796cdc7-a1c0-5e39-bdc0-ddbf5a2f03c1.title: Rotations Per Minute
6796cdc7-a1c0-5e39-bdc0-ddbf5a2f03c1.description: A sensor that measures RPM (rotations per minute) of a rotor.

86a3685d-7309-589c-9621-355fa9e6a0bc.title: Satellite Navigation System
86a3685d-7309-589c-9621-355fa9e6a0bc.description: A satellite-based navigation system like GPS, Gallileo, ...

8a69edcf-e683-544f-96de-29cb8d8ba89b.title: Sensor Aggregator
8a69edcf-e683-544f-96de-29cb8d8ba89b.description:
Aggregate data from multiple sensors into a single stream
(often used as input to machine learning models on the same device, see model runner service).

55b073b0-979a-5b84-a7b0-25abec80b8d8.description:
An asynchronous serial communication service capable of sending and receiving buffers of data.
Settings default to 115200 baud 8N1.

f08f271e-14fb-5f95-8248-4afb64da2b7c.title: Servo
f08f271e-14fb-5f95-8248-4afb64da2b7c.description:
Servo is a small motor with arm that can be pointing at a specific direction.
Typically a servo angle is between 0° and 180° where 90° is the middle resting position.

The `min_pulse/max_pulse` may be read-only if the servo is permanently affixed to its Jacdac controller.

3c464ed9-1d2a-5773-84d1-7fd86b11f2ea.title: Settings
3c464ed9-1d2a-5773-84d1-7fd86b11f2ea.description: Non-volatile key-value storage interface for storing settings.

b497ab94-7c8d-55fa-8b31-f0490461ae9a.title: 7-segment display
b497ab94-7c8d-55fa-8b31-f0490461ae9a.description: A 7-segment numeric display, with one or more digits.

db30efe0-4c78-5440-a97b-5ce6d1ac7ce4.title: Solenoid
db30efe0-4c78-5440-a97b-5ce6d1ac7ce4.description: A push-pull solenoid is a type of relay that pulls a coil when activated.

c333f34d-183d-56c8-b4a7-8b3578a5433c.title: Sound level
c333f34d-183d-56c8-b4a7-8b3578a5433c.description: A sound level detector sensor, gives a relative indication of the sound level.

491b0fad-23f6-5c61-8ba9-08abb8cea995.title: Sound Recorder with Playback

6a91021e-979f-5a7d-bf50-cd3d3898dcd4.title: Sound Spectrum
6a91021e-979f-5a7d-bf50-cd3d3898dcd4.description: A microphone that analyzes the sound specturm

f6d49f8b-688d-5151-a0fc-02dccf27bb94.title: Switch
f6d49f8b-688d-5151-a0fc-02dccf27bb94.description: A switch, which keeps its position.

785ed670-e86d-5cd9-a11f-991dc41cd667.title: TCP
785ed670-e86d-5cd9-a11f-991dc41cd667.description: Data transfer over TCP/IP and TLS stream sockets.

7f9beb07-bd8a-5243-b43f-c79f63c927bd.title: Temperature
7f9beb07-bd8a-5243-b43f-c79f63c927bd.description: A thermometer measuring outside or inside environment.

95610cff-04ba-5cd9-99f9-21a24efe28c6.description:
Supports aggregating timeseries data (especially sensor readings)
and sending them to a cloud/storage service.
Used in DeviceScript.

Note that `f64` values are not necessarily aligned.

afe95bfa-3acf-5aed-b452-2dfc1b2b102b.title: Traffic Light
afe95bfa-3acf-5aed-b452-2dfc1b2b102b.description: Controls a mini traffic with a red, orange and green LED.

19c11808-9b37-5b29-b6c7-ff8a4691a3f1.title: Total Volatile organic compound
19c11808-9b37-5b29-b6c7-ff8a4691a3f1.description: Measures equivalent Total Volatile Organic Compound levels.

91f41451-781e-5be1-8abe-f3399c403a29.title: Unique Brain
91f41451-781e-5be1-8abe-f3399c403a29.description:
The presence of this service indicates that this device is a client that controls sensors and actuators.
If a unique brain detects another younger unique brain (determined by reset counter in announce packets),
then the older brain should switch into proxy mode.

8fc17b4b-9983-53b3-8b31-180fde6c0bd5.title: USB Bridge
8fc17b4b-9983-53b3-8b31-180fde6c0bd5.description:
This service is normally not announced or otherwise exposed on the serial bus.
It is used to communicate with a USB-Jacdac bridge at the USB layer.
The host sends broadcast packets to this service to control the link layer.
The device responds with broadcast reports (no-one else does that).
These packets are not forwarded to the UART Jacdac line.

Packets are sent over USB Serial (CDC).
The host shall set the CDC to 1Mbaud 8N1
(even though in some cases the USB interface is connected directly to the MCU and line settings are
ignored).

The CDC line carries both Jacdac frames and serial logging output.
Jacdac frames have valid CRC and are framed by delimeter characters and possibly fragmented.

`0xFE` is used as a framing byte.
Note that bytes `0xF8`-`0xFF` are always invalid UTF-8.
`0xFF` occurs relatively often in Jacdac packets, so is not used for framing.

The following sequences are supported:

* `0xFE 0xF8` - literal 0xFE
* `0xFE 0xF9` - reserved; ignore
* `0xFE 0xFA` - indicates that some serial logs were dropped at this point
* `0xFE 0xFB` - indicates that some Jacdac frames were dropped at this point
* `0xFE 0xFC` - Jacdac frame start
* `0xFE 0xFD` - Jacdac frame end

0xFE followed by any other byte:
* in serial, should be treated as literal 0xFE (and the byte as itself, unless it's 0xFE)
* in frame data, should terminate the current frame fragment,
  and ideally have all data (incl. fragment start) in the current frame fragment treated as serial

c3ff4408-b4b5-5fb2-9b16-844fe8bf4a7c.description: The UV Index is a measure of the intensity of ultraviolet (UV) rays from the Sun.

1b5fec82-8c99-5534-8b7e-a13992825cee.description: A mixin service that exposes verified telemetry information for a sensor (see https://github.com/Azure/Verified-Telemetry/tree/main/PnPModel).

2f76c8a2-cba7-5dde-b945-1b24deef233f.title: Water level
2f76c8a2-cba7-5dde-b945-1b24deef233f.description: A sensor that measures liquid/water level.

0238d065-1ac9-5887-9aff-f5f30783dcc2.title: WIFI
0238d065-1ac9-5887-9aff-f5f30783dcc2.description: Discovery and connection to WiFi networks. Separate TCP service can be used for data transfer.

e978b9d2-cb9d-5b54-b00d-0ad0fbbbdd0b.title: Wind direction
e978b9d2-cb9d-5b54-b00d-0ad0fbbbdd0b.description: A sensor that measures wind direction.

0d6da511-7ba7-5d29-a344-bf6335695dff.title: Wind speed
0d6da511-7ba7-5d29-a344-bf6335695dff.description: A sensor that measures wind speed.

4fac99d1-ef87-53bf-a974-d1fee7b56ddd.title: WSSK
4fac99d1-ef87-53bf-a974-d1fee7b56ddd.description:
Defines a binary protocol for IoT devices to talk to DeviceScript gateway over encrypted websockets.
This is not used as a regular Jacdac service.
